                               <desc>A fine ornamental band, here and at the incipits of other texts</desc>
                           </decoNote>  
                       
                       <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">                   
                           <desc>A fine miniature of the Virgin with Child, with two angels behind, St Ephrem the Syrian (?) and a donor
                               around, on the folium before the incipit page of the Wǝddāse Māryām</desc>
                       </decoNote>                             
                           
                           <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d6">                   
                               <desc>A fine drawing of a complex composition, which shows the Saviour enthroned, with the Virgin on his side, 
                                   judging the souls (?). The donor (identified as Gabra Śǝllāse) is depicted lying beneath. 
                                   around</desc>
                           </decoNote>                             
